<seg id="60">The above data show that the parallel audits carried out by both countries are directed towards a significant part of public procurement, which is of great financial importance in all procurements, and that open procedure and public tendering are of paramount importance in the award of contracts.</seg>
<seg id="61">Summary of the results of the parallel audits</seg>
<seg id="62">The Supreme Control Office of the Czech Republic (NA) and the Federal Audit Office of the Federal Republic of Germany (BRH) have carried out parallel audits in their countries on the allocation of construction services and the prevention of corruption.</seg>
<seg id="63">In this context, the working groups of both courts of auditors compared the relevant legal bases and administrative requirements in the Czech Republic and Germany, as well as the results of their parallel audits, which they carried out, in particular in the fields of construction and road construction.</seg>
